<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-176-124  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 176 124.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  March 23 1989 v37 n6 p16(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Embedded programming: C or Ada? (Technology Briefing) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Till, Johna.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Assembly language used to be the only language available inprogramming embedded control systems.andP;  The programs were safe anduncomplicated, and higher level languages didn't execute asefficiently.andP;  Faster processors and better compilers have made Cthe programming language of choice for embedded control systems.andO;The highly portable and well-known language executes quickly andefficiently.andP;  Although C may persist as the language of choice inmany cases, Forth, Pascal, and in particular Ada, should all beconsidered for such applications.andP;  Ada can better handle large,complex systems, and with 32-bit machines proliferating, moreefficient compilers are available.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     C Programming LanguageADADesignSoftware EngineeringEmbedded Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>